cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D object detection and pose estimation from RGB images. The use of deep learning methods also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of PnP and RANSAC for pose estimation suggests that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the method on both synthetic and real training data suggests that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
